---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="me" description="About Eddie, frontend engineer and creative builder.">
  <div class="about">
    <article class="about__inner">

    <p class="p--intro">
      I'm Eddie. I've always been the kind of person who needs to be making something. Drawing, building, putting things together. That part has been there for as long as I can remember.
    </p>

    <div class="about-row">
      <div class="about-row__text">
        <p class="p--body p--tilt-left">
          I went to a Waldorf school. Less sitting and reading boring stuff, more making things with your hands and being allowed to think a little sideways. That's where the creative side got its shape. <em>Not being square was kind of the point.</em>
        </p>

        <p class="p--body">
          And there was always a computer nearby. I grew up on them. Gaming, messing around, just living online. Computer-native before that was a word for it. I never really programmed as a kid, but I always cared about how things looked and felt. <em>Aesthetics were never an afterthought.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="about-photo">
        <img
          src="/images/me.jpeg"
          alt="Eddie"
          width="828"
          height="1283"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>
    </div>

    <p class="p--punch p--center">
      Creative first.<br>Code came <strong>later</strong>.
    </p>

    <p class="p--intro">
      Eventually I went looking for the formal version of all this. I did a 2 year Webmaster program at university. Then a 2 year vocational program in frontend engineering. Left four months before the end.
    </p>

    <p class="p--punch">
      Not because it got hard.<br>Because it had <strong>stopped being useful</strong> (or fun).
    </p>

    <p class="p--tilt-left">
      Every placement at a real company meant old codebases, maintenance tasks, and no room to do anything new. I'm a creative person. Constraints are fine. <em>Boredom isn't.</em>
    </p>

    <p class="p--body p--right">
      The other thing that pushed me out: the program had almost nothing to say about AI, even as it was already changing how software gets built. I'd rather be <em>in it than reading about it later</em>.
    </p>

    <p class="p--body">
      I've built the standard stack: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React, some backend, some APIs. The foundation is there.
    </p>

    <p class="p--display">
      design,<br>UI,<br>UX.
    </p>

    <p class="p--body p--tilt-right">
      Not because code doesn't interest me. Problem-solving with code is genuinely satisfying. It's just that the most important thing to me is <em>how something looks and how it feels to use</em>.
    </p>

    <p class="p--punch p--center">
      Frontend sits between<br>design and engineering.<br><strong>That's why it fits.</strong>
    </p>

    <p class="p--body">
      Lately I've been learning on my own. Building real things, experimenting, taking on work for friends and local companies. I've been building plenty with AI, but what actually pulls me in is <em>how it works underneath</em>, not just what it can spit out.
    </p>

    <p class="p--body p--tilt-left">
      I'd rather understand a thing than just use it. So I take it apart, see what it's made of, and put it back together a little better than I found it.
    </p>

    <p class="p--outro">
      <strong>nope studio</strong> is where I do the work.<br>Real things, made <strong>with care</strong>.
    </p>

    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    width: 100%;
    flex: 1;
    background: var(--2);
    color: var(--3);
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  .about__inner {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: var(--max-width-site);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 6rem) var(--space-container) clamp(6rem, 14vw, 12rem);
  }

  .about p {
    font-family: var(--font-family-prose);
    color: var(--3);
    margin: 0;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  /* Large intro paragraph */
  .about .p--intro {
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin-bottom: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  /* Big punchy one-liners */
  .about .p--punch {
    font-family: var(--font-family-base);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-bottom: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  /* Normal body text */
  .about .p--body {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 48ch;
    margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
  }

  /* Right-aligned body */
  .about .p--right {
    margin-inline-start: auto;
    text-align: right;
  }

  /* Giant display word stack */
  .about .p--display {
    font-family: var(--font-family-base);
    font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 12vw, 10rem);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-black);
    line-height: 0.9;
    letter-spacing: -0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-block: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  /* Center-aligned punch */
  .about .p--center {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 100%;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  /* Outro */
  .about .p--outro {
    font-family: var(--font-family-base);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
    line-height: 1.35;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-top: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  /* Text + photo row */
  .about-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin-bottom: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem);
  }

  .about-row__text {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  /* Paragraphs inside the row drop their own bottom margin; the row's gap
     and flex layout handle spacing. */
  .about-row__text p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* Portrait photo */
  .about-photo {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    margin: 0;
    width: clamp(11rem, 26vw, 18rem);
    transform: rotate(2deg);
  }

  .about-photo img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: grayscale(1);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-row {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .about-photo {
      width: clamp(13rem, 60vw, 18rem);
      align-self: center;
    }
  }

  /* Tilt variants */
  .about .p--tilt-left {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.8vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 44ch;
    transform: rotate(-1.5deg);
    margin-bottom: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
  }

  .about .p--tilt-right {
    transform: rotate(1deg);
  }
</style>
